23. In the Cartesian coordinate system $x O y$, the parametric equation of curve $C_{1}$ is $\left\{\begin{array}{l}x=\sqrt{3} \cos \alpha \\ y=\sin \alpha\end{array}\right.$ (where $\alpha$ is the parameter). Establish a polar coordinate system with the origin as the pole and the positive x-axis as the polar axis. The polar equation of curve $\mathrm{C}_{2}$ is $\rho \sin \left(\theta+\frac{\pi}{4}\right)=2 \sqrt{2}$.

(1) Write the ordinary equation of $C_{1}$ and the Cartesian equation of $C_{2}$;

(2) Let point $P$ be on $C_{1}$ and point $Q$ be on $C_{2}$. Find the minimum value of $|P Q|$ and the Cartesian coordinates of $P$ at this time.
